headline: As Artificial Intelligence (AI) Stocks Fall, Investors Should Consider Buying More of These 2 Powerhouses
summary: Artificial intelligence (AI) stocks generally delivered outstanding gains to investors in 2023 and 2024, but due to factors outside their control, this year is turning out to be a more challenging one for them.  However, Nvidia has the ability to outpace those expectations as the demand for its latest generation of Blackwell data center graphics processing units (GPUs) remains robust.
